cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language generation and coherence in narrative story generation.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a reinforcement learning method for learning the skeleton of the story.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques for generating coherent text.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is possible as the paper may use neural networks for generating text.
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely as the paper does not seem to deal with sound or audio data.
